    "Unknown": "). The Word of God graciously and effectually brought Peter `[char_Peter_Mat_4]` to repentance. [v_Luk_22_32] A work of our Advocate \u201cI have prayed for thee\u201d (Luke 22:32). As a great High Priest and Intercessor, the Lord Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` Christ prayed for Peter `[char_Peter_Mat_4]`\u2019s preservation in faith and restoration by grace, even before he fell! That same great High Priest is our Advocate on high. He intercedes for us now, and has interceded for us from eternity (1 [v_Jhn_2_1] John `[char_John_Ref]` 2:1, 2). Then, at the time appointed, the Lord Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` came to Peter `[char_Peter_Mat_4]`, made himself known to Peter `[char_Peter_Mat_4]`, and made Peter `[char_Peter_Mat_4]` to know himself (John `[char_John_Ref]` 21:15-17). These thoughts thrill my heart and flood my soul with joy! The `[group_Canaanites_Gen_10]` Lord Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` Christ is full of tenderness and mercy. His faithfulness is great. And his compassions never fail. He who is our God and Saviour is a faithful, unfailingly faithful God and Saviour! If you are a believer, if truly you trust Christ alone as your Lord and Saviour, nothing shall ever separate you from him, not even [v_Rom_4_8] your sins (Romans 4:8). Nothing can separate us from his love, his favour, his mercy, or his care. Nothing can ever sever you from his saving power or his forgiveness. And nothing can ever tear you from his omnipotent hand of grace! The Signs Of Peter `[char_Peter_Mat_4]`\u2019s Restoration The Lord\u2019s works for and upon Peter `[char_Peter_Mat_4]` were effectual. They accomplished their intended design. And Peter `[char_Peter_Mat_4]` was graciously restored by the very Saviour he so vehemently denied. Peter `[char_Peter_Mat_4]`\u2019s trial and fall were not accidents. Satan ran God\u2019s child through his rough sifter; but Peter `[char_Peter_Mat_4]` lost nothing in the process but chaff. Peter `[char_Peter_Mat_4]` came out of this thing a much better man than he was before, as the book of Acts demonstrates. Even this tragic affair was under the control of God\u2019s sovereign providence and according to his purpose of grace. Satan is God\u2019s devil. That fiend of hell is the unwilling, unwitting [v_Isa_14_12] [v_Isa_14_13] [v_Isa_14_14] [v_Isa_14_15] [v_Isa_14_16] [v_Isa_14_17] [v_Isa_14_18] [v_Isa_14_19] [v_Isa_14_20] [v_Isa_14_21] [v_Isa_14_22] [v_Isa_14_23] [v_Isa_14_24] [v_Isa_14_25] [v_Isa_14_26] [v_Isa_14_27] vassal of the Almighty (Isaiah `[char_Isaiah_Gen_26]` 14:12-27). Let us never forget that fact for a moment. The dragon of hell is as much included in all things working together for good to God\u2019s elect as the angels of [v_Rom_8_28] light (Romans 8:28). Peter `[char_Peter_Mat_4]` went out of the place ("
